scripts.name: ScrollScript
scripts.rawScript:
end
:touch
play "gfdg#f#d#agea#g#f-gfdg#f#d#agea#g#f-gfdg#f#d#agea#g#f"
scroll bold "Welcome, Adventurer!"
scroll "Your quest begins here, in the strangely low-resolution Village of JZT."
scroll "Your task is to locate the five purple keys hidden throughout this mysterious village. These keys will unlock the five purple doors leading to the Hidden  Palace of JZT. This palace is said to contain untold wealth as a reward for deserving adventurers, and you just might be up to the task!"
scroll "Getting to the palace will not be easy, however. An ancient scroll known only as CodePage 437 warns that ferocious creatures and intricate puzzles stand in the way to whomever dares seek the treasure."
scroll "There are a few things you need to know before embarking on such a dangerous journey..."
scroll bold "Exploring"
scroll "The world of JZT is full of strange and wonderful items. If you don't know what something is, try touching it. As someone very wise once said, the worst that can happen is... death!"
scroll bold "Your Health"
scroll "You begin your quest with a paltry 50 health points, which will be reduced by 10 each time you're injured. Once you reach zero health points, I'm afraid it's curtains for you and your adventure!"
scroll "Luckily, you can recover health points by collecting gems (1 point each), up to your maximum. There are also several hearts hidden throughout the village which will increase your maximum health by 10 points each--if you're lucky enough to find them!"
scroll bold "Defending Yourself"
scroll "To survive in this strange land, you're going to need a weapon. Luckily you've got your trusty zapper by your side! Less luckily, it seems, your zapper needs ammunition, and you're going to have to find it."
scroll "Once you've got some ammo, though, you can shoot by holding down the SPACE key and pressing an ARROW key in the direction you want to shoot. Easy, right?"
scroll bold "Saving Your Game"
scroll "Of course, you should expect to meet an unfortunate demise when embarking on such a perilous journey. To avoid having to restart from the beginning, it would be wise to save your game regularly."
scroll "Save your game by pressing the [S] key at any time during your adventure. It is strongly recommended to keep several save points throughout your journey. It's possible to find yourself stuck and unable to continue, so saving often may be your only chance for success!"
scroll bold "The Purple Keys"
scroll "Keys in the land of JZT are enchanted (for some reason), allowing you to only carry one of each color at a time. This means that once you find a purple key, you need to bring it immediately to the palace to unlock a purple door. Once you get into the palace, your quest will be nearly over."
scroll bold "More help..."
scroll "If you need more help, please feel free to consult the gameplay manual or support forums on the JZT website at any time."
scroll bold "Best of luck, adventurer!"
scroll bold "You'll need it!"
end

Welcome to Main Street.

scripts.name: BobScript
scripts.rawScript:
// Bob, the shopkeeper
//
// Offers items in exchange for gems
// and advice for free.

end

:touch
    scroll bold "Welcome to Bob's Discount Stuff Mart!"
    scroll "Is there anything I can get ya?"
    scroll "Ammo: 20 shots.................20 gems" ammo
    scroll "Torches: 5 torches.............10  gems" torches
    scroll "Health: 10 health..............50 gems" health
    scroll "Gossip and advice.................free" gossip
end

:ammo
    take 20 gems toopoor
    give 20 ammo
    say "Thanks a million, friend!"
end

:torches
    take 10 gems toopoor
    give 5 torches
    change torch empty
    zap torches
    say "Thanks! Those are my last ones!"
end

:torches
    say "I'm afraid I'm sold out..."
end

:health
    take 50 gems toopoor
    give 10 health
    say "Thanks, bud!"
end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "If you ever come across some darker walls that are full of cracks, try shooting them. They tear down pretty easily."
    scroll "I've got lots more gossip and advice, so come back any time and ask for more!"
    end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "I've heard that pressing [P] not only pauses the game, but will also show you some vital statistics. Whatever that means..."
    end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "If you're searching for the purple keys, I'd head to the marsh first. It's south of the crossroads, but there's a troll blocking the way... If only someone would get rid of that bully once and for all!"
end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "\"It's absolutely vital that you save often.\" That's what my grandmother used to tell me. She was a wise woman."
end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "Have you ever tried to use your zapper, only to hear a weird clicking sound instead? It's a bizarre phenomenon, for sure!"
    scroll "As far as I can tell, some areas only allow a few shots out at a time before your zapper jams. Elsewhere, it seems that you could unload as much ammo as you'd like. I find the inconsistency annoying, to say the least..."
end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "I once visited a room that was so dark, I couldn't see a thing! If only I had a torch, I could have pressed [T] to illuminate the area around me."
end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "I heard that there's a secret passage in the zoo, but I haven't bothered to check it out myself. I'm simply too busy. Besides, the zoo is 10 whole spaces away."
end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "Cheat codes, you say? I've never heard of them. Perhaps you're thinking of another, completely different world whose passing resemblance to this one is almost certainly coincidental."
end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "I've heard that there are items, enemies and terrains that you won't encounter in the Village of JZT, but that exist nonetheless. Perhaps those are better left to another adventure."
end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "Ever since teleporters were invented, I've had a tough time wrapping my head around how they work. Sometimes they act like a one-way door, and other times they zap you across the room."
    scroll "To be perfectly honest, I'm too afraid to even use one. I mean, what if stepping through one just replaces you with an identical copy of yourself? Everyone I know that has used one claims it works, of course, but that's exactly what I'd expect a copy to say."
end

:gossip
   zap gossip
   scroll "There's a cave just south of the palace path, but it's extraordinarily dark inside. If I were you, I'd use my torches judiciously. My stock here is limited, so I really can't sell you very many."
end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "Teleporters aren't the only bit of newfangled technology around these parts. Duplicators are a hot new item, and they can make copies of whatever is behind them. They're usually used to make a bunch of enemy creatures, though."
    scroll "Duplicating gems and items is possible, of course, but strictly illegal. Not that anyone can tell a counterfeit from its original -- it would just \"disrupt our entire economy,\" according to our mayor. Politics, amiright?"
end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "The zoo has a snake which is a hit with visitors, but there's a whole ranch full of them to the northeast."
end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "Back when I was young, I used to clear out whole patches of forest just for fun. I wonder if anyone else does that?"
end

:gossip
    zap gossip
    scroll "What happens if you run out of ammo or torches? Well, I guess you just can't shoot or see in dark areas, I guess. One of the many reasons you should save often, I suppose."
end

:gossip
   scroll "That's all the advice I've got, I'm afraid. Of course, if you want to hear any of that again, just let me know."
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
   restore gossip
end

:toopoor
    scroll "I'm afraid you don't have enough gems. Perhaps I could interest you in something else?"
end

tiles.text: Lions generally move around haphazardly, but some are more intelligent than others.
Tigers, as we all know, act very much like lions do, but also carry guns.

Bears like to hibernate, but will charge toward you if you find yourself aligned with them.
Fun Fact: Bears will tear down breakable walls if they're in the way, but then will immediately die of exhaustion.
Ruffians dart about erratically, charging at their prey with bursts of speed.
Snakes... don't seem to do much, do they?

Centipedes, naturally, crawl about and take several shots to defeat.
Fun Fact: If you split a centipede in two, it becomes two centipedes. We at the zoo recently found this out, which is why there are two here today.

scripts.name: TreasureKeeper
scripts.rawScript:
// Always look for gems
:loop

   if not exists gem endgame
   send loop

// When touched...
:touch

   play "sg#ab+c#-ibsag#iaf#g#e"
   scroll "Congratulations, adventurer!"
   scroll "You've reached the fabled treasure room, filled with gems more valuable than any item in any videogame ever created."
   scroll "Collect them all. You deserve it!"

   send loop

// Victory!
:endgame

   lock
   char 0
   say "Well done! 5000 bonus points!"
   give 5000 score
   play "exxxexexexxxexexexexexxxexx"
   
   change blue breakablewall empty
   change blue wall breakablewall
   change blue solidwall wall
   change brightblue solidwall wall
   change brightred wall breakablewall
   change brightred solidwall wall

   wait 5

   change brightblue wall breakablewall
   change blue breakablewall empty
   change blue wall breakablewall
   change brightred breakablewall empty
   change brightred wall breakablewall

   wait 5

   change brightblue breakablewall empty
   change blue breakablewall empty
   change brightred breakablewall empty

   wait 10
 
   victory
